## Adjusting Stats for Story

### Narrative Importance

**Minor Threat:** Lower end of baseline, reduce Vitality
**Recurring Villain:** Higher Vitality, add escape options (teleport, hidden exits, loyal bodyguards)
**Climactic Adversary:** Upper end of baseline, add unique abilities

### Dramatic Needs

**Chase Scene:** High movement, lower Vitality (they should escape)
**Social Conflict:** High Presence/Mind, moderate combat stats
**Siege Defense:** Very high Vitality, lower damage (needs to survive prolonged fighting)
**Assassination Attempt:** Very high damage, low Vitality (glass cannon)

### Story Logic

**Ancient Guardian:** Very high Vitality (survived centuries)
**Hired Thugs:** Low loyalty (flee when hurt), respect strength
**Zealot Cultists:** Fight to death regardless of stats
**Corrupt Official:** High social skills, minimal combat ability

### Party Capabilities

**Party Has Healing:** Enemies can hit harder
**Party Focuses Single Target:** Add reinforcements or escape options
**Party Uses Area Effects:** Use fewer, tougher enemies
**Party Struggles with Saves:** Reduce enemy save-or-suck abilities

